title: Yellowjackets Tabbed Fourth in WIAC Poll
text:
Yellowjackets Tabbed Fourth in WIAC Poll 
By Zach Schneider Yellowjackets Tabbed Fourth in WIAC Poll October 20, 2015 Updated Oct 20, 2015 at 5:05 PM CDT 
Superior, WI (NNCNOW.com) --- The UW-Superior men's hockey team has been picked fourth in the Wisconsin Intercollegiate Athletic Conference (WIAC) preseason coaches' poll, which was released on Tuesday afternoon. 
UW-Superior returns 14 letterwinners from last year's team that went (9-18-1), including last year's leading scorer in Anton Svensson. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Dan Stauber is entering his 16th season with the Yellowjackets, and the first win of this year will be his 250th with the program. 
Defending champion UW-Stevens Point is the league's preseason favorite, that after the Pointers advanced to last season's NCAA Division III championship game. 
UW-Superior officially opened practice for the 2015-16 season on Monday.
